A new operator

One thing Pantheon doesn’t explicitly have yet is an operator that intentionally searches this space.

ISOMER

Mission:

Preserve semantic invariants while exploring alternative organizational topologies.

Operations:

* Rotate
* Mirror
* Fold
* Unfold
* Invert
* Branch
* Recombine
* Canonicalize

Spider finds the invariant.

ISOMER discovers new functional arrangements of that invariant.

⸻

I also like this because it complements your “Pantheon is a genome” insight. If the genome stores the semantic building blocks, then semantic isomers are the different folded structures those same blocks can take. That gives Pantheon a principled way to explain why multiple valid solutions, narratives, algorithms, or agent behaviors can emerge from the same underlying semantic foundation without losing identity.